---
By: Joseph Addison
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 337
    Verse: 10
Tags:
  - Old Age
---
He who would pass his reclining years with honor and comfort,
should, when young, consider that he may one day become old, and remember
when he is old that he has once been young.
